headline: Intuitive Surgical shares jump after beating Q4 expectations
summary: The robotic surgery pioneer posted adjusted earnings per share of $2.53, significantly above the analyst consensus of $2.26. Revenue climbed to $2.87 billion, exceeding the $2.75 billion estimate and marking a 19% increase compared to $2.41 billion in the same quarter last year. The strong performance was driven by a 17% growth in da Vinci procedures and a 44% jump in Ion procedures.

headline: Intuitive Surgical beats quarterly estimates on demand for surgical robots
summary: Intuitive Surgical on Thursday beat Wall Street estimates for fourth-quarter profit and revenue on ​growing demand for its surgical robots used in minimally ‌invasive procedures.  Shares of the Sunnyvale, California-based company rose 3.3% in after-hours trading.  The ‌medical device maker has seen consistent growth as hospitals work through a backlog of deferred procedures and expand access to minimally invasive care.

headline: Intuitive Surgical (NASDAQ:ISRG) Delivers Impressive Q4 CY2025
summary: Medical technology company Intuitive Surgical (NASDAQ:ISRG) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 18.8% year on year to $2.87 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.53 per share was 11.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
